'''Suijin Ōhashi''' (水神大橋) is a bridge spanning the [[:en:Sumida River|Sumida River]], carrying a spur of the {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 461|ja|東京都道461号吾妻橋伊興町線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolitan Route 461|qq=}}. The western end of the bridge is located in {{ill|Minami-Senju|ja|南千住|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minami-Senju|qq=}} 8-chōme, Arakawa Ward, while the eastern end is in Tsuijidō 2-chōme, Sumida Ward. The bridge's name originates from the nearby {{ill|Sumidagawa Shrine (Suijin-gū)|ja|隅田川神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumidagawa Shrine (Suijin-gū)|qq=}}, also known as Suijin-gū.
The bridge was first constructed in March 1989 (Heisei 1). Its assembly was carried out on land, and the bridge girders were transported on barges to the site, where tidal changes were used to place them on the piers.
Nearby parks, {{ill|Shioiri Park|ja|汐入公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shioiri Park|qq=}} and {{ill|Higashi Shirahige Park|ja|東白鬚公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Higashi Shirahige Park|qq=}}, serve as disaster response bases for Tokyo. As part of the disaster preparedness plan, Suijin Ōhashi was built alongside {{ill|Senju Shioiri Ōhashi Bridge|ja|千住汐入大橋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senju Shioiri Ōhashi Bridge|qq=}} to connect these parks. Initially a pedestrian-only bridge, it was opened to vehicular traffic on July 10, 1996 (Heisei 8), following the completion of the connecting roads.
On its eastern side, Suijin Ōhashi connects to the [[:en:Mukojima Route|Shuto Expressway Mukōjima Line]] at the {{ill|Tsuijidō Entrance|ja|堤通出入口|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuijidō Entrance|qq=}}.
This location was historically home to the ferry crossing "{{ill|Suijin no Watashi|ja|水神の渡し|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suijin no Watashi|qq=}}."
== Bridge Specifications == * '''Type''': Steel road bridge * '''Structure''': Three-span continuous Nielsen-Lohse girder arch bridge * '''Length''': 157.0 meters * '''Main span''': 102.0 meters * '''Width''': 17.0 meters * '''Construction started''': 1984 (Shōwa 59) * '''Completed''': March 1989 (Heisei 1) * '''Project owner''': Tokyo Metropolitan Government * '''Design''': Tokyo Engineering * '''Girder fabrication''': [[:en:Mitsubishi Heavy Industries|Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]]
== Public Transportation == * '''[[:en:Toei Bus|Toei Bus]]''' ** {{ill|Route 40|ja|都営バス南千住営業所#錦40系統|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Route 40|qq=}}: [[:en:Minami-Senju Station|Minami-Senju Station]] East Exit - Sumida 2-chōme - Shirahige Bridge - Higashi Mukōjima Hirokōji - [[:en:Tokyo Skytree Station|Tokyo Skytree Station]] Front - [[:en:Kinshichō Station|Kinshichō Station]] Front
== Nearby Bridges == * [[:en:Sumida River|Sumida River]] : (Upstream) - {{ill|Sumida River Bridge (Tokyo Metro Hibiya Line)|ja|隅田川橋梁 (東京地下鉄日比谷線)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumida River Bridge (Tokyo Metro Hibiya Line)|qq=}} - {{ill|Senju Shioiri Ōhashi Bridge|ja|千住汐入大橋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senju Shioiri Ōhashi Bridge|qq=}} * '''Suijin Ōhashi''' - {{ill|Shirahige Bridge|ja|白鬚橋|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shirahige Bridge|qq=}} - {{ill|Sakura Bridge (Tokyo)|ja|桜橋 (東京都)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakura Bridge (Tokyo)|qq=}} - (Downstream)
